1
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:03,820
Once the transfer order was official,

2
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:08,220
the preparations went smoothly.

3
00:00:10,120 --> 00:00:14,040
Seeing everything in boxes
makes it feel real all of a sudden.

4
00:00:16,240 --> 00:00:19,040
I haven't spoken to Fukami since then.

5
00:00:25,140 --> 00:00:28,640
I just don't have the confidence.

6
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:34,059
Being long-distance and unable to meet...

7
00:00:34,060 --> 00:00:37,240
Once that connection is gone,

8
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:39,260
there's no way it'll work out.

9
00:00:41,220 --> 00:00:44,840
Someone like me, who wasn't
even loved by his parents...

10
00:00:45,540 --> 00:00:48,560
"There's no such thing as a parent
who doesn't love their child."

11
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:52,020
Looking at you and your sister,

12
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:58,040
it's obvious you were raised
with love in a good home.

13
00:00:59,540 --> 00:01:01,030
It's like a constant reminder

14
00:01:01,230 --> 00:01:03,320
that I'm not like you guys.

15
00:01:05,580 --> 00:01:08,740
I'm the one who hurt you.

16
00:01:11,260 --> 00:01:12,260
No.

17
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:13,280
I don't want this.

18
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:15,360
I don't want to be apart from you.

19
00:01:16,020 --> 00:01:18,100
Don't abandon me.

20
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:22,540
I've had enough of this.

21
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:25,140
I'm tired of being jerked around by you.

22
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,500
Let's just...

23
00:01:34,020 --> 00:01:35,960
end it.

24
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:51,300
Someone who says they aren't confident
they can make you happy...

25
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:53,700
would never be chosen anyway.

26
00:01:56,840 --> 00:02:01,840
There's nothing left for me to do.

27
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:08,860
Is the pollen already acting up?

28
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:09,960
Ah.

29
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:19,050
"Unexpectedly Naughty Fukami"

30
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:25,000
(Episode 9)

31
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:28,560
Bro, are you going to invite
Kaji-san to the wedding?

32
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,079
Why would I?

33
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:37,180
Because he's one of your few friends.

34
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:41,130
By the time the wedding rolls around,

35
00:02:41,330 --> 00:02:43,760
he won't be here anymore.

36
00:02:43,950 --> 00:02:44,950
Huh?

37
00:02:46,660 --> 00:02:47,900
He's transferring.

38
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:51,300
I heard he's going to Hokkaido.

39
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:57,159
So, what are you going to do about it?

40
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:58,919
What do you mean?

41
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:00,699
He's just a colleague.
There's nothing to do.

42
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:01,700
You're lying.

43
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:05,040
You've never introduced
a friend to me before.

44
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:08,500
He's someone important to you, isn't he?

45
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:18,300
He doesn't seem to smile much around me.

46
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:23,060
He's always got a scowl on his face.

47
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:27,860
Maybe things have been hard for him.

48
00:03:31,340 --> 00:03:32,780
So, it's better this way.

49
00:03:34,340 --> 00:03:36,060
Well, of course it is. That's what love is.

50
00:03:37,340 --> 00:03:38,190
Falling for someone

51
00:03:38,191 --> 00:03:39,940
isn't always about being happy.

52
00:03:41,140 --> 00:03:43,039
There's pain, sadness,

53
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,940
and plenty of embarrassing moments.

54
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,180
That's just part of being in love.

55
00:03:49,260 --> 00:03:51,780
Not everyone can do "fast-food" romance,

56
00:03:53,540 --> 00:03:56,340
switching partners like they're
turning a page! Some people can't!

57
00:03:58,060 --> 00:04:00,600
Don't lecture me based on your standards.

58
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,620
We all die in the end anyway.

59
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:08,589
At Mom's funeral,

60
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:11,340
didn't you say you can't take
anything with you when you die?

61
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:15,880
You shouldn't choose to be alone.

62
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,049
I know it's easier that way,

63
00:04:18,050 --> 00:04:19,540
and you don't get hurt as much.

64
00:04:32,020 --> 00:04:34,360
It's not like I'm choosing
to be alone on purpose.

65
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,040
It's just...

66
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:44,120
if he can't be happy with me...

67
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:46,540
Bro.

68
00:04:47,660 --> 00:04:48,860
Thank you for everything.

69
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:51,409
I'll still be back every now and then.

70
00:04:51,410 --> 00:04:54,040
I look forward to seeing you all then.

71
00:04:55,460 --> 00:04:57,719
Kaji-san,
thank you for all your hard work here.

72
00:04:57,720 --> 00:05:00,439
- Thank you.
- Don't catch a cold in Hokkaido!

73
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:02,099
- I won't.
- When you come back,

74
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:03,599
don't forget to bring some crab!

75
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:05,159
Crab, right. You got it.

76
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:05,780
Good luck out there!

77
00:05:05,781 --> 00:05:06,799
I'll do my best.

78
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,276
We'll work hard enough
for you too, Kaji-san.

79
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:10,899
- I'm counting on you.
- Please don't forget about us!

80
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:13,020
I won't.

81
00:05:13,740 --> 00:05:15,219
Hey, don't cry.

82
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:16,700
Oh, good.

83
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:18,119
I made it in time.

84
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:21,939
- Manager Tokura.
- This is a farewell gift from Engineering.

85
00:05:21,940 --> 00:05:23,479
Oh?

86
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:24,559
Are you sure?

87
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:27,199
Of course. You've really looked out for us.

88
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,580
No, it was nothing.

89
00:05:28,940 --> 00:05:30,040
Thank you so much.

90
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:32,239
Can I open it now?

91
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:33,240
Go right ahead.

92
00:05:36,380 --> 00:05:38,000
It's a scarf.

93
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:39,970
Since I'm going somewhere cold,

94
00:05:39,971 --> 00:05:41,211
this will really come in handy.

95
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:45,999
Fukami has better taste than I thought.

96
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,080
Huh?

97
00:05:48,380 --> 00:05:50,720
I heard you and Fukami were close,

98
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:53,299
so I figured he'd know your style.

99
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:54,880
I left the choice up to him.

100
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:58,160
You know how Fukami usually dresses...

101
00:06:01,660 --> 00:06:03,680
I was a little worried after I asked him.

102
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:09,200
But he actually has great taste.

103
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:24,960
Good work today.

104
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:27,440
You too.

105
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:32,339
I heard you picked out the scarf for me.

106
00:06:32,340 --> 00:06:36,060
It was nothing. I just bought
what the clerk recommended.

107
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:41,220
Hey.

108
00:06:42,420 --> 00:06:44,740
Wait for me behind the station after work.

109
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:49,960
I have overtime.

110
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:53,560
I'll wait until you show up.

111
00:06:55,180 --> 00:06:57,969
Are you looking for one last hookup?

112
00:06:57,970 --> 00:06:58,970
Idiot.

113
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,839
What are you saying in a place like this?

114
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,400
If that's what it is, I'll go.

115
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:05,120
But...

116
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:08,240
if it's not,

117
00:07:10,220 --> 00:07:12,470
then I'm not going.

118
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:18,600
Huh?

119
00:07:18,601 --> 00:07:19,719
What?

120
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:21,600
If you come, I'm fine with doing it.

121
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:25,360
But if I go, does that mean
this is the last time?

122
00:07:28,020 --> 00:07:29,869
Because if you don't show up,

123
00:07:29,870 --> 00:07:33,020
we might never get to talk again.

124
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:42,500
I only barely brushed his shoulder...

125
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:45,510
Hey.

126
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:50,560
I'm about to lose it.

127
00:08:05,970 --> 00:08:06,970
Fukami.

128
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:12,359
You're the type who
really would wait forever.

129
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,950
It's scary.

130
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:24,479
Two grown men running
through a crowd hand-in-hand...

131
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,120
People are going to stare.

132
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,840
I can feel people turning to look.

133
00:08:31,660 --> 00:08:33,220
We might even run into someone we know.

134
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:39,420
But I don't care about any of that anymore.

135
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:57,440
Sorry.

136
00:08:57,450 --> 00:08:58,870
Wait.

137
00:09:00,220 --> 00:09:01,720
I'm not ready yet.

138
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:06,020
I want to clean myself out properly.

139
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:11,080
Since it's the last time.

140
00:09:27,160 --> 00:09:29,160
Is this really the last time?

141
00:09:35,990 --> 00:09:39,070
Checking in on how the other person
feeling,

142
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:45,440
showing respect...

143
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:50,900
Fukami taught me all of that.

144
00:10:27,870 --> 00:10:28,870
Ah.

145
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:31,280
So beautiful.

146
00:10:33,660 --> 00:10:35,130
Sorry to keep you waiting.

147
00:10:52,780 --> 00:10:54,080
Forget about that.

148
00:10:55,140 --> 00:10:56,440
If we're doing this, let's go.

149
00:10:58,840 --> 00:10:59,840
Fukami.

150
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:04,540
Can we be friends forever?

151
00:11:12,260 --> 00:11:13,920
Sorry.

152
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:16,440
I'm being so inconsistent.

153
00:11:18,380 --> 00:11:19,380
But you know,

154
00:11:21,460 --> 00:11:25,760
my life has always been full of lies.

155
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:36,079
Being with someone as genuine as you

156
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:38,300
makes me feel like I can finally breathe.

157
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:40,900
So,

158
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:46,380
staying in touch with
you is important to me.

159
00:11:48,820 --> 00:11:51,360
We can meet up and
sleep together sometimes.

160
00:11:52,860 --> 00:11:54,420
I don't care if you see other people.

161
00:11:56,140 --> 00:11:57,910
If it makes things too complicated,

162
00:11:58,110 --> 00:11:59,580
we don't even have to have sex.

163
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:04,540
So, please, just stay in my life...

164
00:12:15,350 --> 00:12:19,350
Let's not be friends.

165
00:12:30,340 --> 00:12:31,400
Sorry.

166
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,720
I'm being annoying, aren't I?

167
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:46,620
Our final night

168
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:49,020
is about to begin.

169
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,500
(Next Episode Preview)

170
00:12:52,580 --> 00:12:54,260
Is this what love is?

171
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,180
Is it always this messy and confusing?

172
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:05,960
So, did you find your answer?

